  "id": "indus_cisi_anchored_6_ko",
  "name": "Indus CISI: Anchored Decipherment — 6 Anchors, P332='o' (ko bigram vowel)",
  "description": "Extends the optimal 5-anchor set with P332='o' based on critical structural evidence: P332 is 100% MEDIAL and appears after P324 in 91% of cases (10/11). P324(/k/) + P332(/o/) = 'ko' (king/chief) — a CV bigram representation of the royal title sign. P332 is the vowel component completing the 'ko' syllable. This is structurally motivated unlike the failed 10-anchor additions. The 6-anchor set: P385->n (genitive), P324->k (initial consonant), P122->a (medial vowel), P086->m (initial consonant), P060->i (medial vowel), P332->o (ko-completing vowel). Test: does adding P332='o' improve or worsen consistency vs 5-anchor? 'k->o' is a common Dravidian bigram so this should improve. GPU: n_seeds=8, max_iter=12000.",
